<title>||kabbo (Jantje) in the train</title>
<summary>||kabbo (Jantje) goes on a journey in a train to Simonstown. He meets  a woman who stops him from falling out of the train, as well as a black man and a white man, each of whom he describes. The black man asks him where he comes from and he answers that his place is the &apos;Bitterpits&apos;.</summary><comments>1) This story is found in Book II</comments><date>1871</date><storypages>355-358</storypages><category>History (personal)</category><category>Relations with others</category><author>||kabbo (Jantje) (II)</author><keyword><kw>train</kw><subkw>&apos;fire wagon&apos;</subkw></keyword>
